Exercise

1) Create and Run a Thread using Runnable Interface and Thread class and show usage of sleep and join methods in the created threads.
2) Use a singleThreadExecutor, newCachedThreadPool() and newFixedThreadPool() to submit a list of tasks and wait for completion of all tasks.
3) Use Synchronize method and synchronize block to enable synchronization between multiple threads trying to access method at same time.
4) WAP to show usage of Callable and demonstrate how it is different from Runnable
5) Write a program to simulate a deadlock in java and then improve the program to handle the deadlock using reentract lock.